<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Outline-style: inherit</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/ui.html#propdef-outline-style" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Outline-style with value inherit uses its parent's outline-style value." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                outline: 0 dotted;
            }
            #div2
            {
                outline: 15px green;
                outline-style: inherit;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is green dotted outline around the following text.</p>
        <div id="div1">
            <div id="div2">Filler Text</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>